Who knew… I actually made the nice list this year.

Week 1 of 2024
Already my year has been filled with friends, laughter, smiles, but also tears. I’m so incredibly blessed to have these people in my life as they mean the whole world to me. It’s always been hard to find people with the same energy and I’m glad I found mine. Decadence with Kylan was so much fun:) seeing a friend from Omaha always warms my heart. Especially Ky. Finally getting to see Liana again after a couple weeks made my entire week. People come and go but I’m blessed to have found some of my forevers. 
Dexter, my pup of 18 years sadly passed away the morning of January 5th. But in my dream last night we were running through flower fields and I think it was his way of coming back and saying goodbye to me since I wasn’t able to be there with him. Pictured is the last time I saw him, Thanksgiving of 2023, and then us when I was little and I used to make him match my outfits. I’m happy he’s no longer in pain and he’s able to run and play again, even though when he left he took a big part of my heart with him.
2024 and to my Forevers❤️
